On the topic. I've been trying to implement a feature to check in the public IP on port 8088 has been forwarded (is open). I've tried this function using Node's native `net` module:

```
var portOpen = (port, host) =>
  new Promise(resolve => {
    var server = net.createServer(socket => {
      socket.write('Echo server\r\n')
      socket.pipe(socket)
    })

    server.listen(port, host)
    server.on('error', e => {
      console.log('error', e)
      resolve(false)
    })
    server.on('listening', e => {
      console.log('workss', e)
      server.close()
      resolve(true)
    })
  })
```

and the [node-telnet-client](https://github.com/mkozjak/node-telnet-client). But both seem to fail at accurately checking. In the command-line `telnet` seems to accurately check... but I can't seem to get it right on NodeJS.

Any tips [@cel-desktop](@lOUVT+Phkvai9a/cCS/RKo+S9hnPAQdVixms/7ldpPA=.ed25519)?

